Hyundai to Expand Turkey Plant for Two New Models, Vatan Says

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-03-03T07:00:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/hyundai-to-expand-turkey-plant-for-two-new-models-vatan-says.html
  Hyundai Motor Co. (005380)  is expected to
announce an investment of less than $500 million within two
months to expand its plant in northwestern  Turkey  to produce two
new models, Vatan newspaper reported, citing Ali Kibar, chairman
of Kocaeli-based Hyundai Assan joint venture.  The new plant, to be completed within 20 months after the
decision is announced, will provide employment for at least
1,000, Kibar said at the Geneva car show, according to the
Istanbul-based newspaper. Hyundaiâ€™s Turkish partner Kibar
Holding will maintain its 30 percent share in the new
investment, Vatan quoted Kibar as saying.   Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
